<br>
Any suggestions on where to go? Which spells to buy? and can I buy all my lvl 8 spells in FP? I'm a  Gnome. <p><img src=http://fp.geocities.com/magnifield_plaid/Boleek2.gif
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umatches475.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Matches475</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(3/18/01 8:02:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tactics for lvl 10-15 Mage</span><hr size=1> It all depends...   What is the race of the necro?  If it is a Dark Elf, some places could cause a few problems, but here is what my necro partner and I did.<br>
<br>
lvls 8 to to 12...   either hunt in EC near the hidden inn (darkweed snakes, wisps, YKs, and spiders) or go to WC and hunt wisps and anything else that comes by.  <br>
<br>
By level 12 we were hunting wisps only.  They are great money for those levels (especially since both of us were playing non-twinked secondary characters).  Towards 14 or 15 the xp slows down a lot.  We moved to Oasis and got in an orc highway group just to hit lvl 16.  <br>
<br>
At lvl 16 (if the necro is not a DE) go to nek forest.  Kill the single spawn guard by the lavastorm zone.  With a partner you could also kill some of the guardians (I was here solo for a bit and I could, but I couldn't keep up with the guard spawn then) while waiting for the guard to spawn.  The xp was good solo until about 18, so it won't be bad with a partner.  The loot was always a bronze weapon, and every once in a while I would loot words or the such.<br>
<br>
If the necro is a dark elf, go to gargoyle island.  Fear Kiting is NOT an option here.  Keep that in mind and you will get gargoyle eyes (8pp to everyone with a cha better than a gnomes).  The xp will be amazing and the spawns will be easy to keep up with.  Just watch out for the spectres (the reason fear kiting is not an option).  They stay at the top of the mountain and so you shouldn't go up there.  <br>
Gargoyle island will support you up towards the mid twenties.<br>
<br>
The summoning spells will have to be bought in Akanon for you, but that isn't too big of a deal...  As for which spells (I bought them all because I want a complete spell book when I am done), the only one that I didn't use a lot (ever actually) was eye of zomm.  A rule of thumb is that all spells have a place to be used, but some are a lot more useful than others.  As for the spells, all spells but summoning (not sure about pets...) can be bought in FP, but the summoning spells are only sold at libraries.  <br>
<br>
Dim pocket is good if you have a stable connection, and loot a lot of heavy stuff from critters (like those bronze weapons).<br>
Pets...   need I say more?<br>
Flame bolt and shock of blades...  bread and butter for a while.<br>
Invisibility and Lesser shielding will save your life a lot.<br>
Renew elements and shield of fire are great pet buffs/heal...  the shield is good for anyone or anyone's pet.<br>
<br>
Since I wasn't real sure if you were asking about which lvl 8 spells to buy or lvl 12, I included both sets.  The only ones that I do not use a lot are Cancel magic (never had a need at this lvl except my brief stay in Lavastorm, but it will come in handy later), Column of fire (I personally do not like AoE spells with 0 range, but that is just play style...), summon fang (will used a lot more when my pet started dual wielding...), and ward summoned (except in my brief time in lavastorm again.).<br>
<br>
I hope this helped, and I am sorry that it is so long, but I tried to fit in all the answers that I could to your questions.  Happy Hunting <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sydia>Sydia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(3/18/01 8:46:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Tactics</span><hr size=1> Matches475 pointed out a lot of good spots.  I'm not going to repeat what he said, but I will give a little advice...<br>
<br>
When you kill wisps, save your greater lightstones and do the quest in North Karana...you can get about 8pp a stone that way.  And good xp.<br>
<br>
Once you hit 16, go to OOT.  This is a great zone to take care a lot of items.  One, kill mermaids for a little while and get the scale you need for your focus test.  Two, kill lots of gargoyles.  Be sure to save one of the eyes for your focus quest.  The island next to sister island has a stone building that has a vender that sells both your 16 and 20th level spells.  Also, shout to the zone and find out who is hunting Gornit.  Ask them if you can loot the toes.  You need all 4 toe types(hill, cyclops, frost, fire) for your focus quest.<br>
<br>
